-- Play Resumes at Soldier Field in Chicago After Tornado Threat
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2013-11-17T20:30:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-17/play-resumes-at-soldier-field-in-chicago-after-tornado-threat.html
Play resumed in a National Football
League game between the Bears and Baltimore Ravens after the
threat of a tornado passed at Soldier Field in Chicago.  Play was halted for one hour, 53 minutes after Justin
Tucker kicked a 52-yard field goal to give the Ravens a 10-0
lead with less than five minutes to play in the first quarter.
 Ray Rice  earlier scored a touchdown for the visitors on a one-yard run.  The game was suspended at 12:32 p.m. local time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  